==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Survival
<hw>Sur*viv"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Survive</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A living or continuing longer
than, or beyond the existence of, another person, thing, or event; an
outliving.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arhaeol. & Ethnol.)</fld> <def>Any habit, usage, or
belief, remaining from ancient times, the origin of which is often
unknown, or imperfectly known.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The close bearing of the doctrine of <qex>survival</qex> on the
study of manners and customs.</q> <rj><qau>Tylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Survival of the fittest</b></col>. <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<cd>See <cref>Natural selection</cref>, under
<er>Natural</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Survivancy</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Survivance</ent>⟦br⟧
